## Verification checklist

> *Drill instrument — fold mentally once green. The rest of this document is the artifact a reader picks up cold; this section is for the drill operator.*

- [ ] One-screen test — anatomy diagram fits one terminal screen
- [ ] One-sentence test — scope reminder is one sentence
- [ ] Refusal-list completeness — every box ≥2 items
- [ ] Joint completeness — every arrow has real default + test double
- [ ] Walk test — every walk step references only objects/messages in the drawing
- [ ] Red-shape test — acceptance test fails on assertions, not plumbing
- [ ] Bypass-audit honesty — ≥3 named risks with mitigations
- [ ] Timer test — drill stayed under ~30 minutes

When all eight pass, write the acceptance test stub; that ends the drill.

